Hello all, Here is the FMEA presentation from JUMPSTART. The presentation in live format should be up on FUN Network’s Youtube channel in the coming days - please watch for it. We have a fail faster database we add to at each event. Here’s our Chezy Champs 2022 Fail Faster database.

We review these items in the week or two after each event. It helps remind us of pain points in the moment of a busy tournament.

Definitely helpful, definitely worth implementing something similar.

docs.google.com

Best,

-Mike

thanks Joe. I know FMEA techniques. For systems that do not have high potential for killing people: I am not a fan. Easy to get tedious, trivial, and waste a lot of time. I am a bigger fan of of fishbone/5 whys/ and other diagnostics method. My sticking point now is convincing someone (student?) to log stuff so we can react from facts later. Will be reading Mike Cs reply soon.
